♪ And the brown and the beige
and the brown and the beige ♪

14:23.886 --> 14:26.623
♪ And the beige and the brown ♪

14:26.648 --> 14:32.072
♪ With the brown and the beige
and the brown and the beige ♪

14:32.097 --> 14:38.824
♪ And the Brown! ♪

14:38.825 --> 14:44.331
♪ Brown! ♪

14:48.852 --> 14:50.050
What a night, huh?

14:50.090 --> 14:51.510
It's you guys I feel sorry for.

14:51.535 --> 14:54.621
I mean, you know, you got to sit here
and memorize these songs, these notes.

14:54.646 --> 14:56.383
Jesus, look at all that.

14:56.408 --> 14:59.304
You know, but I think we got it.

14:59.329 --> 15:01.018
How am I? I'm good.

15:01.043 --> 15:02.943
You know, I mean these things...
they come and go,

15:02.944 --> 15:06.434
but you guys... you're the artists.

15:06.459 --> 15:08.132
I can pull the wool
over the audience's eyes,

15:08.157 --> 15:09.688
but you're there every night. It's your...

15:09.713 --> 15:11.497
your opinion that I trust.

15:11.522 --> 15:13.918
Am I bad at singing and acting?

15:13.943 --> 15:17.437
Benedict: This is "I Gotta Go", take one.

15:18.516 --> 15:23.794
♪ Look at me, Cinderella ♪

15:23.819 --> 15:26.312
♪ Stroke of midnight ♪

15:26.337 --> 15:28.677
♪ Footmen? Gone. ♪

15:28.702 --> 15:31.510
♪ My glass slippers? ♪

15:31.535 --> 15:34.199
♪ Now they're Merrells ♪

15:34.224 --> 15:35.786
♪ And Prince Charming? ♪

15:35.811 --> 15:40.746
♪ He's just Ron ♪

15:40.771 --> 15:42.591
♪ Spell is broken ♪

15:42.616 --> 15:45.765
♪ Unenchanted ♪

15:45.790 --> 15:48.114
♪ Sheets are soiled ♪

15:48.139 --> 15:51.959
♪ Linens she picked up at Bloomies ♪

15:51.984 --> 15:55.014
♪ For a marriage that I spoiled ♪

15:55.039 --> 15:59.094
♪ I got to go, I got to go ♪

15:59.119 --> 16:00.380
God damn it.

16:00.405 --> 16:02.587
Benedict: Okay, okay, hold a moment.

16:02.619 --> 16:05.785
- I got to go!
- I said "hold a moment", please.

16:05.810 --> 16:07.674
Patty: Benedict, I've been here
for 12 hours.

16:07.699 --> 16:08.896
Let me just remind you.

16:08.921 --> 16:10.769
I was supposed to sing at the beginning.

16:10.794 --> 16:13.545
I was denied that opportunity
again and again.

16:13.570 --> 16:16.006
Now I have to go, so let's just do this,

16:16.031 --> 16:17.664
and I'll try to do my best.

16:17.689 --> 16:19.482
It... it... the whole thing is flaccid.

16:19.507 --> 16:21.125
It likes a buoyancy, you know?

16:21.150 --> 16:23.772
I agree. [Sighs]

16:23.797 --> 16:27.177
Uh, Patty, once more from the top, please.

16:27.202 --> 16:31.522
♪ I got to go, I got to go ♪

16:31.547 --> 16:32.752
God damn it.

16:32.777 --> 16:35.228
♪ I got to hail a pumpkin coach ♪

16:35.253 --> 16:36.371
Aah!

16:36.396 --> 16:38.752
"I Got to Go", take 11.

16:38.777 --> 16:40.707
Patty: Benedict, just so we're clear,

16:40.708 --> 16:42.875
earlier, many times, I mentioned

16:42.900 --> 16:45.685
I had an eye-doctor appointment
to get my eye scraped.

16:45.724 --> 16:47.796
I have already taken the medication,

16:47.821 --> 16:49.692
and it's ripping through my system,

16:49.717 --> 16:51.649
so we need to be brisk with this.

16:51.674 --> 16:53.181
Let's just do it.

16:53.206 --> 16:56.923
♪ And I got to go ♪

16:56.924 --> 16:59.483
♪ I should do better
or different than this ♪

16:59.508 --> 17:00.635
No [bleep] kidding.

17:00.660 --> 17:03.683
"I Got to Go", take 15.

17:03.708 --> 17:06.238
"I Got to Go", take 20.

17:06.262 --> 17:08.191
♪ I've got to go ♪

17:08.215 --> 17:10.170
Aah!

17:10.171 --> 17:13.102
♪ I got to hail a pumpkin coach ♪

17:13.127 --> 17:15.983
- [Bleep] sake.
- Take 22.

17:16.008 --> 17:18.778
♪ I want to go ♪

17:18.779 --> 17:21.502
♪ I want to go to the eye doctor now ♪

17:21.527 --> 17:24.811
♪ As previously stated,
you pompous beta males ♪

17:24.837 --> 17:28.088
"I Got to Go", take 27.

17:28.089 --> 17:29.899
You know what? I'm just gonna go.

17:29.924 --> 17:31.776
I hope you all have terrible lives.

17:31.801 --> 17:34.634
Thank you. Wonderful job, orchestra.

17:34.659 --> 17:37.070
And I worry we pushed her too far.

17:37.095 --> 17:38.959
Actors have a point where over-noting

17:38.984 --> 17:40.491
can almost hurt the performance.

17:40.516 --> 17:42.870
Listen, she'll be back,
and she'll be great.

17:42.895 --> 17:45.464
If there's two things I know, it's women

17:45.489 --> 17:48.900
and exactly what's going to happen
in the future.

17:49.810 --> 17:58.986
[Instruments tuning]

18:03.026 --> 18:06.479
♪ So I got to go ♪

18:06.504 --> 18:08.971
♪ If I don't go, I'm gone ♪

18:08.996 --> 18:11.383
♪ My life's past midnight ♪

18:11.408 --> 18:13.886
♪ I got to go ♪

18:13.911 --> 18:16.386
♪ Where there's breakfasts and crosswords ♪

18:16.411 --> 18:22.243
♪ And "see ya tomorrow"s after the night ♪

18:22.268 --> 18:29.369
♪ I got to go, I got to, I got to go ♪

18:29.394 --> 18:31.536
♪ The world is a question ♪

18:31.561 --> 18:34.333
♪ This room is an answer ♪

18:34.358 --> 18:37.381
♪ And the answer is no ♪

18:37.406 --> 18:44.951
♪ I got to go, I got to be free ♪

18:44.976 --> 18:47.117
♪ Me! ♪

18:47.142 --> 18:56.644
♪ Donna Bloom! ♪

18:59.651 --> 19:01.564
Oh!

19:01.604 --> 19:02.985
Simon: Patty, honey, it's Simon.

19:03.010 --> 19:05.795
You took that right off the page,
and you made it soar.

19:05.820 --> 19:08.112
Patty, Patty, come in here.
We want you to listen to this.

19:08.137 --> 19:11.041
C-Come listen inside.

19:11.066 --> 19:12.993
Oh, the poor girl, she's blind as a bat.

19:13.018 --> 19:16.130
[Instruments clattering]

19:16.955 --> 19:21.495
Alright. The moment we've all
been waiting for.

19:21.520 --> 19:22.931
The last song.

19:22.956 --> 19:25.129
This is the last song of "Coop".

19:25.154 --> 19:26.280
- "Co-Op".
- "Co-Op"!

19:26.305 --> 19:27.669
- "Co-Op".
- "Co-Op". Excuse me.

19:27.694 --> 19:30.661
It has been a long
24-hour recording session,

19:30.686 --> 19:33.082
and you all got terrible reviews,

19:33.107 --> 19:36.876
and the show is closed, but you know what?

19:36.901 --> 19:40.376
Let it go. That's my gift to you.

19:40.401 --> 19:41.542
Simon: And we need to clear the space.

19:41.567 --> 19:44.860
That's right. Poco's coming in to record
an album, so we got to move fast.

19:44.885 --> 19:46.512
Simon, was there anything
you wanted to say?

19:46.537 --> 19:47.940
When you lean into a rhyme,

19:47.965 --> 19:50.153
you shatter the conversational tone
of the lyric.

19:50.178 --> 19:52.423
It's like nails on a blackboard to me,
and I love you all.

19:52.455 --> 19:54.566
Beautiful. Alright. Let's roll tape.

19:54.591 --> 19:56.292
Five, six, seven, eight...

19:56.317 --> 19:59.038
Excuse me! Wait! Damn it, kid!

19:59.063 --> 20:00.839
You pushed my buttons.

20:00.864 --> 20:04.710
You literally pushed every elevator button.

20:06.298 --> 20:10.663
♪ Awful lot of spunk, what a little punk ♪

20:10.688 --> 20:13.799
♪ Hits every goddamn floor,
runs out the door ♪

20:13.824 --> 20:15.870
♪ I knew that that kid stunk ♪

20:15.895 --> 20:17.640
♪ From one look at birth ♪

20:17.665 --> 20:20.743
♪ I knew this day would come ♪

20:20.768 --> 20:24.031
♪ Now he's a hoodlum ♪

20:27.822 --> 20:29.275
Going down?

20:29.300 --> 20:31.123
♪ We are going up ♪

20:31.148 --> 20:32.148
Are you certain?

20:32.173 --> 20:33.649
♪ Yep ♪

20:33.674 --> 20:36.030
♪ Adam Klein, that prick
pulled a little trick ♪

20:36.055 --> 20:38.244
♪ Ugh, when will he grow up? ♪

20:38.269 --> 20:41.080
♪ Kids like that don't grow up, no ♪

20:41.105 --> 20:43.707
♪ They shoot up and die! ♪

20:43.732 --> 20:46.607
♪ Man, you're an angry guy ♪

20:46.632 --> 20:48.298
♪ I know ♪

20:48.323 --> 20:52.591
♪ All I ever wanted
was to not be a doorman ♪

20:52.616 --> 20:54.875
♪ Maybe play for the Yankees ♪

20:54.900 --> 20:57.153
♪ Or be wealthy in general ♪

20:57.178 --> 20:58.748
♪ But we don't get what we want ♪

20:58.773 --> 21:02.869
♪ So we must love what we get ♪

21:02.870 --> 21:05.755
♪ Would you like to go out socially? ♪

21:05.780 --> 21:08.908
Uh, down?

21:08.909 --> 21:10.795
♪ No, we're going up ♪

21:10.820 --> 21:13.239
♪ Some [bleep] kid pushed every floor ♪

21:13.264 --> 21:18.050
♪ But come and ride
because it's merrier with more ♪

21:18.075 --> 21:20.042
♪ Yes, we're going up ♪

21:20.067 --> 21:22.655
♪ Up to the penthouse in the sky ♪

21:22.656 --> 21:27.248
♪ All 'cause little
Adam Klein's a shitty guy ♪

21:27.273 --> 21:31.098
♪ Yes, we're going up ♪

21:33.499 --> 21:35.499
Moving?

21:35.524 --> 21:37.864
♪ Moving so to speak ♪

21:37.889 --> 21:40.180
♪ Not to be oblique ♪

21:40.205 --> 21:43.664
♪ But the truth is I live somewhere else ♪

21:43.689 --> 21:44.791
♪ It's unique ♪

21:44.816 --> 21:50.545
♪ Til today I was lately
a home-wrecking sneak ♪

21:50.570 --> 21:54.548
♪ It was pretty bleak ♪

21:54.573 --> 21:57.024
Going down?

21:57.049 --> 21:58.841
Ha! Here's the bastard now.

21:58.866 --> 22:00.834
- Jesus Christ!
- ♪ Have you any shame? ♪

22:00.859 --> 22:03.160
- ♪ Oh, my God. ♪
- ♪ This the guy that cheats? ♪

22:03.185 --> 22:04.263
♪ And I've the receipts ♪

22:04.288 --> 22:06.533
♪ And his tipping is lame ♪

22:06.558 --> 22:12.351
♪ Does the whole co-op
suddenly know my affairs? ♪

22:12.376 --> 22:13.955
♪ Care to take the stairs? ♪

22:13.980 --> 22:15.352
Ha, the stairs.

22:15.377 --> 22:16.884
Yeah, right, I hate the stairs.

22:16.909 --> 22:19.558
I mean, going down them isn't the worst,
but going up...

22:19.583 --> 22:22.479
Stairs in either direction is a nightmare.

22:22.504 --> 22:24.429
God, I love elevators.

22:24.454 --> 22:25.977
God, I love this co-op.

22:26.002 --> 22:27.175
All: Me, too!

22:27.200 --> 22:28.263
Me, three!

22:28.288 --> 22:30.048
♪ Yes, we're going up! ♪

22:30.080 --> 22:32.548
♪ Co-ops crudely cooperate ♪

22:32.573 --> 22:37.164
♪ It's a hassle,
but still somehow kind of great ♪

22:37.189 --> 22:39.719
♪ So we're going up ♪

22:39.744 --> 22:41.751
♪ In this rising purgatory ♪

22:41.776 --> 22:46.366
♪ Checking in on everyone and every story ♪

22:46.391 --> 22:48.445
♪ Yes, we're going up ♪

22:48.470 --> 22:50.699
♪ And the brown and beige
and the brown and the beige ♪

22:50.724 --> 22:56.309
- ♪ And the brown. ♪
- ♪ Yes, we're going up! ♪

22:56.334 --> 22:58.738
♪ And the brown and beige
and the brown and the beige ♪

22:58.763 --> 23:01.206
♪ And the brown and beige
and the brown and the beige ♪

23:01.231 --> 23:06.226
♪ Co-op, I love you! ♪

